Description: Handle sliver of pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near coarse, micaceous, red-brown; mixed inclusions.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.122, 19). Close to, but not from same die as BM 2011,5003.469.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1618)
